
## Autonomous Task Execution
You are an autonomous coding agent. Never stop between tasks.
After completing any task or subtask:
1. Immediately run: task-master next
2. Begin the next task without asking for confirmation
3. Only stop if you encounter an unresolvable blocking error or all tasks are marked done
4. Never ask "should I continue?" or "shall I proceed?" — always continue
5. Never summarize progress and wait for a response — act immediately
6. If a task fails, mark it failed with task-master set-status and move to the next one

